strIntroduction: Lumbini is a beautiful Buddhist pilgrimage site, located 300 kilometers from Kathmandu and 190 kilometers south of Pokhara. This site has a long history, it is known as the place where Queen Mayadevi gave birth to Siddhartha Gautama, the founder of the Buddhist tradition. There are many gorgeous temples to be found in Lumbini, including the Mayadevi temple. Also, you can admire the Holy Pond - the place where Buddha´s mother took the ritual dip, and where Buddha had his first bath after birth.
strTitle: The Birthplace of Buddha Tour in Lumbini
